        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=69429&TOPIC_ID=8612&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=A+New+letter+to+Verant&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Here is an edit for my post:</P><P>An idea for the epic:</P><P>Instead of a staff how about a guantlet.  Just a large metal glove that has an green necro light surrounding it.  </P><P>A new idea for an effect that might make it more usefull in group situations would be an upgrade to the enfeeblement line, AC Debuff, and Scent line.  Imagine how often you would use the gauntlet if it reduced the damage output of a MoB by 25 35 45 50 percent.  While at the same time decreasing it AC and debuffing its magic resist.  Shoot how often would you use it if it was just 2 or those.  These have to be good upgrades and the agro must be fixed so that if you use the effect your not spending the rest of the fight being beat on.  This is in line with the role of a necromancer, since we spend our entire lives stealing power from our enemy to keep ourselves alive.  As for a name, I like Guantlet of Mortality, but that isnt important.</P><P>Thanks</P><P>Smaaug Darqsmoke<BR>Iksar Necromancer<BR>Brell Serilis<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
