        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=69431&TOPIC_ID=8612&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=A+New+letter+to+Verant&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">#1  Pets -<BR>       1.  Hitpoints should be about 50% higher for the post-50 pets.<BR>       2.  Lifetaps should actually work.<BR>       3.  Pets behavior should be fixed, specifically, pets should actually /follow you closely no matter what zone or geography you're in, and not behave erratically or causing aggro to mobs outside your radius of pet control.<BR>       4.  The /pet hold command should NOT be a skill, but something included in the game since it was first introduced.</P><P>#2 Epic Weapon -<BR>       1.  And "epic" weapon shouldn't be a topic for humorous discussion.  The graphic and visual effects need to be fixed so they appear as impressive as intended.</P><P>#3  Spells -<BR>        1.  Usefulness of the spells Infusion and Trucidation does not balance against the component cost.<BR>        2.  Replacements for the spells Ignite Bones and Chill bones drop too rarely from mobs of unnecessarily high level.<BR>        3.  The ratio of mana-transfer spells can be improved.<BR>        4.  Fear immunity should come with the spell Arch Lich, justifying it's usefulness in the game as something other than a novelty.<BR>        5.  Quivering Veil of Xarn should be castable anytime.  With the night-time restriction 99.9% of Necromancers don't even memorize or attempt to obtain this spell.</P><P><BR>Wish List -<BR>        1.  A difficult-to-obtain darkness spell near level 60 which is a faster-casting DOT/Snare would be a welcome addition, since most Necros don't use anything stronger than Dooming Darkness due to cast time.<BR>        2.  Re-evaluation of the group spells recently added.  The vast majority of Necromancers find ourselves sorely disappointed at the real usefulness of any of these spells.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
