        <br><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1"><small> </small></font>
        <br><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1"><small>148 Posts</small></font></td>
        <td bgcolor="dimgray" colspan="2" ><img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;12/12/2001&nbsp;:&nbsp; 02:01:28</font>
        
		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=2285"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=2285')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=69750&TOPIC_ID=8612&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=A+New+letter+to+Verant&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">In no particular order....</P><P><BR>1) Chardok spell drops. Too rare for spells which are purely cosmetic and can not be considered upgrades in any sense of the word. Why wasn't at least the level 44 spell put on a vendor?</P><P>2)Pets. New graphic is terrible, change please. Ac/Hp/attk needs increasing on 53/56/59 pets. Pet lifetap needs fixing. All necromancer pets from roleplay perspective should be immune to fear - would certainly make sense more if 49+ pets were immune not just 59.</P><P>3) Essence emeralds. Vague justification for rez spell needing this component. All other spells which use it are firmly placed on page 50 of my spellbook or not even scribed. Worthwhile spell line? I think not.  </P><P>4) Night time only spells. Totally agree with indoor/outdoor limitations - but why do necros have nighttime restrictions? Innoruuk doesn't work a shift system or none of my spells would work during the day.</P><P>5) Spells. We need a dd upgrade which is not mob type specific. Not a stupidly powerful one by any means but I can't think of any other caster class which tops out in nukeage at level 44 with a spell which had all the justifications for its reycle time nerfed.</P><P>6) Epic. The epic look stinks, the effect is a joke and really I cannot see any reason to pursue my epic further. Even the stats cannot persuade me to wander around with a duck stick and face the ridicule of every level 5 in east commons when I can look much more suave and sophisticated with a gbs in that slot. Give us an epic which the majority would aspire to.</P><P>7) Melee dmg versus Necro damage. I chose this class knowing that I was trading ac/hp in return for dealing damage. Due to mob resists and the length of most encounters, I am lagging well behind most tanks in damage dealing. More fast acting, low aggro dots please.</P><P>8) Dot stacking. We get lots of dots. Problem is that with the exception of the bond line none stack with the dots of other necros and even higher level sks (bond gives you the hp but does no extra damage when stacked). This kind of reduces the demand and need for necromancers. Allow more dots of same line to stack when cast by different necros.</P><P>9) If coffins are available now in SoL from the vendors, could they not also be introduced into more old world zones?</P><P>10) Bonechip vendors please. The economy on many servers is so devalued that east commons and neriak are populated by twinks who destroy bonechips not sell them. We don't see mages or beastmasters farming pet components do we?</P><P>11) Pet aggro - why does it switch from mob to mob so much? In dungeon groups this is fatal problem. Any way in which a command can be introduced to tell pet to stay on one mob for group situations?</P><P>12) /pet hold ought to be a general command not a skill. No matter how good a necro you are, your pet will always attack when you are hit. This isn't about making things too easy, it's about letting us group at our full powers without fear of wipeouts.</P><P>13) Plant specific line of spells. Where are the plants? I see things which look like walking begonias but the spell doesn't work on them. This line ought to be reconsidered if you are not willing to be less restrictive on the mobs you are willing to allow us to use it upon.</P><P>14)More research spells post50? Would be nice to see my 200 skill not just be used to make level 34 spells. </P><P>15) DMF restrictions. Abolish the restrictions. Our one and only useful buff for others and even in kedge where you allow mages to summon waterstones by the backpack full we cannot cast it. Seems silly.</P><P>16) SoL group spells - not had chance to test any yet, so I will hold my initial cynicism towards them in check.</P><P><BR>Felly</P><P>Felinaval Dreamweaver<BR>52 Heretic<BR>Mystic Valor<BR>Saryrn Server</P><P>"For in the end we all shall die. Until then let me seek glory!"<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

